.\" Automatically generated from tb source; do not edit manually.
.Dd May 2, 2026
.Dt TB 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm config.toml
.Nd tmpbuffer configuration file format
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Pa $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tmpbuffer/config.toml
.Pp
.Nm
.Pa -c config_path
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
uses a TOML-based configuration file read at startup.
If the file does not exist, sensible defaults are used for all values.
Environment variables override corresponding file settings when both are
present.
.Pp
The default config file path is
.Pa $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tmpbuffer/config.toml .
An alternative path can be specified with the
.Fl c
option to
.Xr tb 1
or
.Xr tmpbufferd 1 .
.Sh FILE FORMAT
The configuration file uses
.Ux
TOML syntax.
The following sections describe the recognised keys.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic editor
External editor command used when opening a buffer with
.Ic tb edit
or the TUI.
.Pp
If this key is not set, the
.Ev EDITOR
environment variable is consulted, followed by
.Ev VISUAL ,
with a fallback to
.Xr vi 1 .
.Pp
Even when this key is set, the
.Ev EDITOR
environment variable still takes precedence at runtime.
.Pp
Default: unset (delegates to
.Ev EDITOR
env var, then
.Xr vi 1 ) .
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
editor = "code --wait"
.Ed
.It Ic preview_command
Shell command used to render buffer content in the TUI preview pane.
The buffer content is piped to this command's stdin and the ANSI-coloured
stdout is rendered via an embedded terminal emulator.
.Pp
Common choices include
.Xr bat 1
.Pq with Fl -color Ns = Ns Sy always
or
.Xr highlight 1 .
.Pp
If not set, the preview pane displays buffer content as plain text.
.Pp
Default: unset (plain text preview).
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
preview_command = "bat --color=always --style=plain"
.Ed
.It Ic time_format
Controls how timestamps are displayed in the TUI buffer list.
.Pp
Acceptable values:
.Bl -tag -width "absolute" -compact
.It Sy relative
Display relative timestamps (e.g.,
.Dq now ,
.Dq 5m ,
.Dq 2h ,
.Dq 3d ) .
.It Sy absolute
Display absolute timestamps (e.g.,
.Dq 14:30
for today,
.Dq 04-28
for earlier days).
.El
.Pp
Default:
.Sy relative .
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
time_format = "absolute"
.Ed
.It Ic trash_ttl_seconds
Number of seconds a buffer remains in the trash before being permanently
deleted.
.Pp
When a buffer is deleted (soft delete), it is moved to the trash rather
than removed immediately. After the trash TTL expires, the buffer is
purged automatically by the daemon's background cleanup goroutine.
.Pp
Set to 0 to disable automatic purging (buffers remain in the trash
indefinitely and must be restored or permanently deleted manually).
.Pp
Default: 86400 (24 hours).
.Pp
Example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
trash_ttl_seconds = 604800  # 7 days
.Ed
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables override the corresponding configuration
file keys at runtime. If both the file key and the environment variable are
set, the environment variable wins.
.Bl -tag -width "TB_TIME_FORMAT"
.It Ev EDITOR
Overrides the
.Ic editor
configuration key.
.It Ev VISUAL
Overrides the
.Ic editor
configuration key if
.Ev EDITOR
is not set. Follows the POSIX convention:
.Ev EDITOR
takes precedence over
.Ev VISUAL .
.It Ev TB_PREVIEW_CMD
Overrides the
.Ic preview_command
configuration key.
.It Ev TB_TIME_FORMAT
Overrides the
.Ic time_format
configuration key (values:
.Ql relative
or
.Ql absolute ) .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "config.toml"
.It Pa $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tmpbuffer/config.toml
Default configuration file location.
If
.Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is not set, the default is
.Pa $HOME/.config/tmpbuffer/config.toml .
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
A comprehensive configuration file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
editor = "vim"
preview_command = "bat --color=always --style=plain"
time_format = "relative"
trash_ttl_seconds = 172800
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr tb 1 ,
.Xr tmpbufferd 1
.Pp
Project repository: https://github.com/szdytom/tb
